- Level editing for RootTux -

Last update: April 29, 2026

This document describes how to use Tiled to edit levels

= LEVEL EDITOR =

USING TILED:
--------------
Tiled is an external project that is used to make levels for
many games including RootTux (or else it wouldn't be mentioned :) ).

Anyway, it is pretty easy to use. So, if you are considering doing 
a few levels for this, it would be a good idea to check this out.

Its webpage is located at:
https://www.mapeditor.org/

You need to make a copy of the base level, then edit it, making sure
all the objects are in the correct object layer and have the correct
class names (you should use the objects in the top part of the level,
however, when you're finished creating your level, you need to delete
the objects there (not the objects inside the level) otherwise when
you begin the level, the objects fall from the sky!)


